cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.OS, cs.SE, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on embedded computing systems and their resource constraints. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses real-time control applications and the use of feedback scheduling to manage resources. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possible category as the paper addresses challenges in software design and programming in multitasking environments. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of feedback schedulers. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the distribution of resources among concurrent tasks.
